Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) pottery rosette(?) bowl; interior glazed orange with added red band lined in white below lip; exterior reserved save part of a vertical preserved in lip zone and a narrow stripe painted on top of lip; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.844)
